<p><b>Lottery mathematics</b> is used to calculate <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Probabilities" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Probabilitie=
s">probabilities</a> of winning or losing a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Lottery" title=3D"Lottery">lottery</a> game. It is based primaril=
y on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorics" title=3D"Combi=
natorics">combinatorics</a>, particularly the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Twelvefold_way" title=3D"Twelvefold way">twelvefold way</a> and=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combination" title=3D"Combination=
">combinations without replacement</a>. It can also be used to analyze coin=
cidences that happen in lottery drawings, such as repeated numbers appearin=
g across different draws.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Pollanen_1-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lottery_mathematics#cite_note-=
Pollanen-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup>
