<div class=3D"shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=
=3D"display:none">Probabilities of winning a lottery game</div>
<p>In the following
</p>
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">P</span> =
is the number of balls in a pool of balls that the winning balls are drawn =
from, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Without_replacement" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Without replacement">without replacement</a>.</li=
>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">W</span> is t=
he number of winning balls drawn from the pool.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">T</span> is t=
he number of balls listed on the lottery ticket.  (It often equals <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">W</span>.)</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">M</span> is t=
he number of balls that match on the lottery ticket and within the winning =
set.</li></ul>
