<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Power_balls_from_a_separate=
_pool_of_balls">Power balls from a separate pool of balls</h2><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLottery_mathematics&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Power balls from a sepa=
rate pool of balls"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Some lotteries also have one or more power balls drawn from a separate p=
ool of balls.  For example, the first drawing may be for <span class=3D"tex=
html"><i>W</i><sub>1</sub> =3D 5</span>&nbsp;balls out of <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><i>P</i><sub>1</sub> =3D 69</span>&nbsp;balls and then <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>W</i><sub>2</sub> =3D 1</span>&nbsp;power ball may be drawn=
 from <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>P</i><sub>2</sub> =3D 26</span>&nbsp;balls=
.  For both pools, the drawing is without replacement.  Similarly a lottery=
 ticket will indicate <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>T</i><sub>1</sub></span>&n=
bsp;regular balls and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>T</i><sub>2</sub></span>&n=
bsp;power balls.  Often the number of balls on the lottery ticket is the sa=
me as the winning set: <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>T</i><sub>1</sub> =3D <i>=
W</i><sub>1</sub></span>&nbsp;and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>T</i><sub>2</s=
ub> =3D <i>W</i><sub>2</sub></span>.  The probabilities of getting <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml"><i>M</i><sub>1</sub></span>&nbsp;matches in the first drawi=
ng and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>M</i><sub>2</sub></span>&nbsp;matches in =
the power ball drawing is just the product of the individual probabilities:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \Pr[M_{1},M_{2}\mid P_{1},T_{1},W_{1},P_{2},T_{2},W_{2}]=3D{\fr=
ac {{T_{1} \choose M_{1}}{P_{1}-T_{1} \choose W_{1}-M_{1}}}{P_{1} \choose W=
_{1}}}{\frac {{T_{2} \choose M_{2}}{P_{2}-T_{2} \choose W_{2}-M_{2}}}{P_{2}=
 \choose W_{2}}}\,,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
