 of balls"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>Some lotteries have one or more bonus balls drawn from the original pool=
 of balls after the first round of balls is drawn.  In this scenario each l=
ottery ticket indicates <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">T</span>&nbsp;balls out of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fon=
t-style:italic;">P</span>&nbsp;possibilities, but the drawing is for <span =
class=3D"texhtml"><i>W</i><sub>1</sub></span>&nbsp;balls plus <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>W</i><sub>2</sub></span>&nbsp;bonus balls, without replacem=
ent.  The probability that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>M</i><sub>1</sub></sp=
an>&nbsp;balls from the first drawing match the lottery ticket and <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml"><i>M</i><sub>2</sub></span>&nbsp;balls from the bonus-ball =
drawing match the lottery ticket is given by
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \Pr[M_{1},M_{2}\mid P,T,W_{1},W_{2}]=3D{\frac {{W_{1} \choose M=
_{1}}{W_{2} \choose M_{2}}{{P-W_{1}-W_{2}} \choose {T-M_{1}-M_{2}}}}{P \cho=
ose T}}\,.}">
